<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-046-226 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 354 345</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Magazine  Oct 1991 v6 n10 p188(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Miller Freeman Publications 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ViruSafe/LAN from XTree. (XTree Co.'s ViruSafe/LAN data securitysoftware)(brief article) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dougherty, Elizabeth; McLean, Michelle.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   XTree Co. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   ViruSafe/LAN (Data security software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionData SecuritySecurity SoftwareComputer Viruses.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ViruSafe/LAN software from XTree detects viruses, removes them, and reportsits actions to the network supervisor.andP;  ViruSafe/LAN version 4.5, developedby EliaShim Microcomputers (Tel Aviv, Israel), runs on Novell NetWare andNetBIOS networks.andM;ViruSafe/LAN monitors memory, file allocation tables, boot sectors, partitiontables, root directories, and executable files for viruses.andP;  The software canrecognize a new virus, learn its signature, and delete it before it gets intothe network.andP;  If a virus attacks ViruSafe/LAN, the software can rebuilditself without being reinstalled.andM;Scans for viruses can be continuous, time-activated, manual, or performedautomatically when a user logs in.andP;  A network manager can configure thesoftware to take actions when it encounters a virus.andP;  For example, thesoftware can report the virus, automatically remove the virus, or delete thefile containing the virus if it can't remove it.andM;A network manager can install an optional 9KB terminate-and-stay-residentprogram on each workstation that uses filters to check for security breaches.andO;For example, the administrator can set filters to investigate memory sizeChanges, check diskettes, and report replication activity.andM;ViruSafe/LAN costs $595 for a 10-user license.andM;XTree, 4330 Santa Fe Rd., San Luis Obispo, CA 93401, (805) 541-0604.andO;</TEXT></DOC>